The program will have an easy-to-use interface that makes it simple for users to input their location and quickly access weather information. 
The program will come with detailed instructions on how to use it, including how to understand the presented weather data.

API Rate Limits: 

The OpenWeatherMap API may have rate limits on the number of requests per minute or per day, 
which could affect the application's performance under heavy usage.

Data Accuracy: 

While the API provides reliable weather data, occasional discrepancies or inaccuracies may occur, leading to potential user frustration.

Cross-Origin Resource Sharing (CORS): 
The application may encounter CORS issues when making requests to the OpenWeatherMap API from a different domain, requiring appropriate handling.
